Place a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} on top rack and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

In a #medium pot{}, combine @farro{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and 3 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> TIP: If you end up with any excess stock, simply pour it out. Alternatively, if stock evaporates before farro is done, add a splash of water.

== Roasted Veggies ==

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and sliced) into 1-inch-thick wedges. Dice @sweet potatoes{2}(diced) into 1/2-inch pieces. In a #large bowl{}, toss veggies with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @chili powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Carefully spread out on preheated baking sheet.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Marinated Cranberries ==

While veggies roast, zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine juice from two lemon wedges and @sugar{1%teaspoon}. Stir in @dried cranberries{1%ounce}. Let marinate, stirring occasionally, at least ~{15%minutes}.

== Dressing and Assembly ==

Once cranberries have marinated, transfer lemon juice marinade to a second large bowl (leaving cranberries in small bowl). Whisk @olive oil{1%tablespoon} into bowl with marinade; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Stir @butter{2%tablespoon}, half the roasted veggies, and half the dressing into pot with farro. Season with salt and pepper.

To bowl with remaining dressing, add @arugula{2%ounce}, cranberries, and remaining roasted veggies; toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide farro mixture between bowls. Top with salad. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @salsa verde sunflower pepitas{1/2%ounce}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.